  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following categories reflect a recommended communication plan structure to define key communication elements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Meeting - the regularly scheduled time at which communication included in this document occurs.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Communication Item - the specific deliverable to be used for communication.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Content Description - explanation of communication component and the content of the component.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Purpose - the goal of communication item.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Frequency - Number of times per period that the communication component should be delivered.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Media - The physical form the information is communicated.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Audience/Attendees - An individual or a group of people who the communication is targeted/distributed.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Responsibility - A person or people who are responsible for establishing the meeting or for formatting,&#xD;
        communicating and distributing the communication item.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Required Approval - Approval requirement of the indicated item required prior to publication or execution?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The plan is typically presented in simple table format.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
